
linger sample container: Receive message, linger for a while (total 1 sec)
                         in critical moments, then echo reply to the caller

This is to demonstrate EBUSY scenario in SIC communication.

Run (load and start) container:

    $ mwtest.py -c100 run sample_linger.img

Create test data:

    $ printf echo.me. > testfile

Send testfile twice to the container:

    $ cmtest data -f100 testfile; cmtest data -f100 testfile

The second pmtest invocation, when reading response from container
will fail with "FAILED: 16: Device or resource busy"

The reason is that the write sent before did not go through as the
container was not yet ready to receive the message. That information
is not known by the caller until it tries to receive reply.

In real-world application should such an improbable case that EBUSY
is received in (response) read, the write request has to be re-sent.

The CMRT HLOS Programmer's Guide contains section "SIC Protocol Scenarios"
which has this request - response service well documented.

Unload container:

    $ mwtest.py -c100 unload
